{
  "_comment": [
    "Batch-2 high-frequency Turkish VERB roots. The aorist allomorph is the documented grammar",
    "default for every entry here, so none carries an explicit 'aorist': vowel-final -> -r",
    "(sağlar, karşılar), polysyllabic consonant-final -> -Ir (ulaşır, gerekir, oluşur, bitirir),",
    "monosyllabic consonant-final -> -Ar (kurar, bozar, dolar, artar, çözer, doğar, ölçer).",
    "The new monosyllables (art, kur, boz, dol, çöz, doğ, ölç) were each checked against the",
    "closed ~13-member -Ir monosyllable list (al/bil/bul/dur/gel/gör/kal/ol/öl/san/var/ver/vur)",
    "and are NOT members, so the -Ar default is correct. Both a base and its lexicalized",
    "causative are listed where both are common (art/artır, azal/azalt) so neither depends on",
    "productive causative generation."
  ],
